So this was the first week that the station is closing at midnight now
And I call bullsheet because the new closing hours were announced less than a week in advance, and 2nd shift was effectively told to suck it up
My one coworker who is way more aggressive on such matters talked with the manager because she was given no notice of a change in her hours
She had to call the store to find out that she'd be in here until past midnight to close up shop
Several problems with this whole arrangement.
1) She lives an hour away, so the soonest she'd get home is probably 1:30

2) She has a small child at home.  And while she is currently living with her mother, her mother is more or less getting ready for work at the same time she's coming home, so there's a potential for her small child to be home alone at 2 in the morning
3) When we were closing the store at 10, one person from second would be running the store solo for an hour, with half an hour to close up.  That is now 3 hours solo followed by half-hour close

4)  The hour change is because the store wants to go back to 24/7, but we have no people willing or able to work overnight.  So these hours will be going on until whenever we can fill the overnight position.
